Building mental resilience involves developing the ability to cope with stress, adversity, and challenges in a healthy and adaptive way. Here are some tools and strategies that can help enhance mental resilience 

1. Mindfulness meditation - 
Description : Mindfulness involves paying attention to the present moment without judgement.
How to use : practice mindfulness meditation regularly. Focus on your breath, sensations in your body, or the environment around you. Mindfulness helps reduce stress and enhances self-awareness.

2. Cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT) -
Description : CBT is a therapeutic approach that helps identify and change negative thought patterns and behaviors. 
How to use : work with a mental health professional trained in CBT or use self-help resources that apply CBT principles to challenge and reframe negative thoughts. 
